    <a data-track="click_references" rel="nofollow noopener" data-track-label="link" data-track-item_id="link" data-track-value="mathscinet reference" data-track-action="mathscinet reference" href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=3306099" aria-label="MathSciNet reference 59">MathSciNet</a> 
    <a data-track="click_references" rel="nofollow noopener" data-track-label="link" data-track-item_id="link" data-track-value="math reference" data-track-action="math reference" href="http://www.emis.de/MATH-item?1311.62094" aria-label="MATH reference 59">MATH</a> 
    <a data-track="click_references" data-track-action="google scholar reference" data-track-value="google scholar reference" data-track-label="link" data-track-item_id="link" rel="nofollow noopener" aria-label="Google Scholar reference 59" href="http://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?&amp;title=Evaluation%20methods%20and%20decision%20theory%20for%20classification%20of%20streaming%20data%20with%20temporal%20dependence&amp;journal=Mach.%20Learn.&amp;doi=10.1007%2Fs10994-014-5441-4&amp;volume=98&amp;issue=3&amp;pages=455-482&amp;publication_year=2015&amp;author=%C5%BDliobaite%2CI&amp;author=Bifet%2CA&amp;author=Read%2CJ&amp;author=Pfahringer%2CB&amp;author=Holmes%2CG">
                    Google Scholar</a> 
                </p></li><li class="c-article-references__item js-c-reading-companion-references-item" data-counter="60."><p class="c-article-references__text" id="ref-CR60">Bifet, A., Holmes, G., Pfahringer, B., Kranen, P., Kremer, H., Jansen, T., Seidl, T.: Moa: massive online analysis, a framework for stream classification and clustering. In: Diethe, T., Cristianini, N., Shawe-Taylor, J. (eds.) Proceedings of the First Workshop on Applications of Pattern Analysis. Proceedings of Machine Learning Research, vol. <b>11</b>, pp. 44–50. PMLR, Cumberland Lodge, Windsor, UK (2010)</p></li><li class="c-article-references__item js-c-reading-companion-references-item" data-counter="61."><p class="c-article-references__text" id="ref-CR61">Klein, S., Verbeke, M.: An unsupervised methodology for online drift detection in multivariate industrial datasets. In: 2020 International Conference on Data Mining Workshops (ICDMW), pp. 392–399 (2020). <a href="https://doi.org/10.1109/ICDMW51313.2020.00061" data-track="click_references" data-track-action="external reference" data-track-value="external reference" data-track-label="10.1109/ICDMW51313.2020.00061">https://doi.org/10.1109/ICDMW51313.2020.00061</a></p></li><li class="c-article-references__item js-c-reading-companion-references-item" data-counter="62."><p class="c-article-references__text" id="ref-CR62">Hutter, F., Kotthoff, L., Vanschoren, J. (eds.): Automated Machine Learning: Methods, Systems, Challenges. The Springer Series on Challenges in Machine Learning. Springer, Cham (2019). <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-05318-5" data-track="click_references" data-track-action="external reference" data-track-value="external reference" data-track-label="10.1007/978-3-030-05318-5">https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-05318-5</a> . Accessed 2024-06-17</p></li><li class="c-article-references__item js-c-reading-companion-references-item" data-counter="63."><p class="c-article-references__text" id="ref-CR63">Theodorakopoulos, D., Stahl, F., Lindauer, M.: Hyperparameter Importance Analysis for Multi-Objective AutoML. <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/2405.07640" data-track="click_references" data-track-action="external reference" data-track-value="external reference" data-track-label="http://arxiv.org/abs/2405.07640">arXiv:2405.07640</a> [cs] (2024). Accessed 2024-06-17</p></li><li class="c-article-references__item js-c-reading-companion-references-item" data-counter="64."><p class="c-article-references__text" id="ref-CR64">Werner, E., Kumar, N., Lieber, M., Torge, S., Gumhold, S., Nagel, W.E.: Towards computational performance engineering for unsupervised concept drift detection—complexities, benchmarking, performance analysis. <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/2304.08319" data-track="click_references" data-track-action="external reference" data-track-value="external reference" data-track-label="http://arxiv.org/abs/2304.08319">arXiv:2304.08319</a> [cs] (2024). Accessed 2024-06-17</p></li><li class="c-article-references__item js-c-reading-companion-references-item" data-counter="65."><p class="c-article-references__text" id="ref-CR65">François Caron: Matlab/Octave package Polyatreetest (2014). <a href="https://www.stats.ox.ac.uk/%7Ecaron/code/polyatreetest/index.html" data-track="click_references" data-track-action="external reference" data-track-value="external reference" data-track-label="https://www.stats.ox.ac.uk/%7Ecaron/code/polyatreetest/index.html">https://www.stats.ox.ac.uk/%7Ecaron/code/polyatreetest/index.html</a>. Accessed 2023-05-04</p></li></ol><p class="c-article-references__download u-hide-print"><a data-track="click" data-track-action="download citation references" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow" href="https://citation-needed.springer.com/v2/references/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y?format=refman&amp;flavour=references">Download references<svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-download-medium"></use></svg></a></p></div></div></div></section></div><section data-title="Acknowledgements"><div class="c-article-section" id="Ack1-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="Ack1">Acknowledgements</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="Ack1-content"><p>We thank Daphne Theodorakopoulos for the code review.</p></div></div></section><section data-title="Funding"><div class="c-article-section" id="Fun-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="Fun">Funding</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="Fun-content"><p>This work was funded by VolkswagenStiftung (Volkswagen Foundation) and Niedersächsisches Ministerium für Wissenschaft und Kultur (Lower Saxony’s Ministry for Science and Culture) under Niedersächsisches Vorab (grant number <i>ZN3683</i>, <i>Change Event based Sensor Sampling</i>).</p></div></div></section><section aria-labelledby="author-information" data-title="Author information"><div class="c-article-section" id="author-information-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="author-information">Author information</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="author-information-content"><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="affiliations">Authors and Affiliations</h3><ol class="c-article-author-affiliation__list"><li id="Aff1"><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__address">Marine Perception, German Research Center for Artificial Intelligence, Marie-Curie-Straße 1, 26129, Oldenburg, Germany</p><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__authors-list">Daniel Lukats, Oliver Zielinski &amp; Frederic Stahl</p></li><li id="Aff2"><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__address">Computing Sciences, Carl von Ossietzky Universität Oldenburg, Ammerländer Heerstraße 114-118, 26129, Oldenburg, Germany</p><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__authors-list">Daniel Lukats &amp; Axel Hahn</p></li><li id="Aff3"><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__address">Leibniz Institute for Baltic Sea Research Warnemünde, Seestraße 15, 18119, Rostock, Germany</p><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__authors-list">Oliver Zielinski</p></li><li id="Aff4"><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__address">Systems Engineering for Future Mobility, German Aerospace Center, Escherstraße 2, 26121, Oldenburg, Germany</p><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__authors-list">Axel Hahn</p></li></ol><div class="u-js-hide u-hide-print" data-test="author-info"><span class="c-article__sub-heading">Authors</span><ol class="c-article-authors-search u-list-reset"><li id="auth-Daniel-Lukats-Aff1-Aff2"><span class="c-article-authors-search__title u-h3 js-search-name">Daniel Lukats</span><div class="c-article-authors-search__list"><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--left"><a href="/search?sortBy=newestFirst&amp;contributor=Daniel%20Lukats" class="c-article-button" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - publication" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">View author publications</a></div><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--right"><p class="search-in-title-js c-article-authors-search__text"><span class="c-article-authors-search__links-text">Search author on:</span><span class="c-article-identifiers"><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=search&amp;term=Daniel%20Lukats" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - pubmed" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">PubMed</a><span class="u-hide"> </span><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://scholar.google.co.uk/scholar?as_q=&amp;num=10&amp;btnG=Search+Scholar&amp;as_epq=&amp;as_oq=&amp;as_eq=&amp;as_occt=any&amp;as_sauthors=%22Daniel%20Lukats%22&amp;as_publication=&amp;as_ylo=&amp;as_yhi=&amp;as_allsubj=all&amp;hl=en" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - scholar" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">Google Scholar</a></span></p></div></div></li><li id="auth-Oliver-Zielinski-Aff1-Aff3"><span class="c-article-authors-search__title u-h3 js-search-name">Oliver Zielinski</span><div class="c-article-authors-search__list"><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--left"><a href="/search?sortBy=newestFirst&amp;contributor=Oliver%20Zielinski" class="c-article-button" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - publication" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">View author publications</a></div><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--right"><p class="search-in-title-js c-article-authors-search__text"><span class="c-article-authors-search__links-text">Search author on:</span><span class="c-article-identifiers"><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=search&amp;term=Oliver%20Zielinski" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - pubmed" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">PubMed</a><span class="u-hide"> </span><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://scholar.google.co.uk/scholar?as_q=&amp;num=10&amp;btnG=Search+Scholar&amp;as_epq=&amp;as_oq=&amp;as_eq=&amp;as_occt=any&amp;as_sauthors=%22Oliver%20Zielinski%22&amp;as_publication=&amp;as_ylo=&amp;as_yhi=&amp;as_allsubj=all&amp;hl=en" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - scholar" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">Google Scholar</a></span></p></div></div></li><li id="auth-Axel-Hahn-Aff2-Aff4"><span class="c-article-authors-search__title u-h3 js-search-name">Axel Hahn</span><div class="c-article-authors-search__list"><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--left"><a href="/search?sortBy=newestFirst&amp;contributor=Axel%20Hahn" class="c-article-button" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - publication" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">View author publications</a></div><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--right"><p class="search-in-title-js c-article-authors-search__text"><span class="c-article-authors-search__links-text">Search author on:</span><span class="c-article-identifiers"><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=search&amp;term=Axel%20Hahn" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - pubmed" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">PubMed</a><span class="u-hide"> </span><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://scholar.google.co.uk/scholar?as_q=&amp;num=10&amp;btnG=Search+Scholar&amp;as_epq=&amp;as_oq=&amp;as_eq=&amp;as_occt=any&amp;as_sauthors=%22Axel%20Hahn%22&amp;as_publication=&amp;as_ylo=&amp;as_yhi=&amp;as_allsubj=all&amp;hl=en" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - scholar" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">Google Scholar</a></span></p></div></div></li><li id="auth-Frederic-Stahl-Aff1"><span class="c-article-authors-search__title u-h3 js-search-name">Frederic Stahl</span><div class="c-article-authors-search__list"><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--left"><a href="/search?sortBy=newestFirst&amp;contributor=Frederic%20Stahl" class="c-article-button" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - publication" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">View author publications</a></div><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--right"><p class="search-in-title-js c-article-authors-search__text"><span class="c-article-authors-search__links-text">Search author on:</span><span class="c-article-identifiers"><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=search&amp;term=Frederic%20Stahl" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - pubmed" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">PubMed</a><span class="u-hide"> </span><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://scholar.google.co.uk/scholar?as_q=&amp;num=10&amp;btnG=Search+Scholar&amp;as_epq=&amp;as_oq=&amp;as_eq=&amp;as_occt=any&amp;as_sauthors=%22Frederic%20Stahl%22&amp;as_publication=&amp;as_ylo=&amp;as_yhi=&amp;as_allsubj=all&amp;hl=en" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - scholar" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">Google Scholar</a></span></p></div></div></li></ol></div><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="contributions">Contributions</h3><p>DL conceived the study, conducted the literature search, implemented the algorithms and experiments, conducted the experiments and analyzed the results. FS reviewed the experiment design and aided in the analysis. AH, FS and OZ provided supervision and aided with the conception of this study. DL took the lead in writing the manuscript. All authors provided critical feedback and helped shape the study, analysis and manuscript.</p><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="corresponding-author">Corresponding author</h3><p id="corresponding-author-list">Correspondence to
                <a id="corresp-c1" aria-label="email Daniel Lukats" href="mailto:Daniel.Lukats@dfki.de">Daniel Lukats</a>.</p></div></div></section><section data-title="Ethics declarations"><div class="c-article-section" id="ethics-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="ethics">Ethics declarations</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="ethics-content">
              
              
                <h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="FPar1">Conflict of interest</h3>
                <p>The authors have no Conflict of interest to declare that are relevant to the content of this article.</p>
              
              
                <h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="FPar2">Ethical approval</h3>
                <p>This research did not involve human participants or animals.</p>
              
            </div></div></section><section data-title="Additional information"><div class="c-article-section" id="additional-information-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="additional-information">Additional information</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="additional-information-content"><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading">Publisher's Note</h3><p>Springer Nature remains neutral with regard to jurisdictional claims in published maps and institutional affiliations.</p></div></div></section><section aria-labelledby="appendices"><div class="c-article-section" id="appendices-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="appendices">Appendices</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="appendices-content"><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="App1">Implementation details</h3><p>In some publications the algorithm description left room for implementation or was at odds with the source code provided by the authors. Furthermore, some algorithms do not adapt to the new concept after a drift. These cases and the respective choices concerning this study’s implementation are outlined below. To understand some of these implementation choices, more in-depth study of the respective publication or the algorithm’s source code may be required.</p><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="Sec37"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.1 </span>BNDM</h3><p>The source code provided by the authors of <i>BNDM</i> uses a Matlab implementation of the Pólya tree test by Caron [<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 65" title="François Caron: Matlab/Octave package Polyatreetest (2014). &#xA;                  https://www.stats.ox.ac.uk/%7Ecaron/code/polyatreetest/index.html&#xA;                  &#xA;                . Accessed 2023-05-04" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y#ref-CR65" id="ref-link-section-d8444539e10554">65</a>]. In this implementation the data is normalized using the median and the interquartile range. If the 25% and the 75% element have the same value, this will lead to a division by zero, which is not addressed by the authors of <i>BNDM</i> [<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 48" title="Xuan, J., Lu, J., Zhang, G.: Bayesian nonparametric unsupervised concept drift detection for data stream mining. ACM Trans. Intell. Syst. Technol. 12(1), 5–1522 (2020). &#xA;                  https://doi.org/10.1145/3420034&#xA;                  &#xA;                " href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y#ref-CR48" id="ref-link-section-d8444539e10560">48</a>] nor by Caron. In this case, this study’s implementation subtracts the median from the sample without adjusting its range.</p><p>The paper and Caron’s Matlab implementation provide different information on the return value when the maximum recursion depth is reached. This study uses the same value as the Matlab implementation.</p><p>A reset mechanism that purges the data windows after a concept drift was added, as explained in Sect. <a data-track="click" data-track-label="link" data-track-action="section anchor" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y#Sec27">5.3</a>.</p><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="Sec38"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.2 </span>CSDDM</h3><p>Occasionally, one of the samples generated for evaluation with the <i>k</i>-sample Anderson-Darling test may be empty. As there is no information regarding this issue in the paper, the hypothesis test is skipped in this case and no concept drift is detected.</p><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="Sec39"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.3 </span>IBDD</h3><p>The authors mention normalization specifically for images, by which they mean transforming the image to grayscale [<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 46" title="Souza, V.M.A., Chowdhury, F.A., Mueen, A.: Unsupervised drift detection on high-speed data streams. In: 2020 IEEE International Conference on Big Data (Big Data), pp. 102–111 (2020). &#xA;                  https://doi.org/10.1109/BigData50022.2020.9377880&#xA;                  &#xA;                " href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y#ref-CR46" id="ref-link-section-d8444539e10591">46</a>]. Since there are no further mentions of normalization, the data is not normalized in this study’s implementation.</p><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="Sec40"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.4 </span>SPLL</h3><p>As part of the Gaussian mixture model a covariance matrix is determined. From the publication, it is not quite clear if this covariance matrix is computed over the entire data or only the reference data. Since the Gaussian mixture model is fit on the reference data only, the implementation for this study computes the covariance matrix on the reference data only as well. A reset mechanism was added by purging the reference data window, as explained in Sect. <a data-track="click" data-track-label="link" data-track-action="section anchor" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y#Sec27">5.3</a>.</p><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="Sec41"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.5 </span>UDetect</h3><p>A reset mechanism that purges the data windows and resets the thresholds after a concept drift was added, as explained in Sect. <a data-track="click" data-track-label="link" data-track-action="section anchor" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y#Sec27">5.3</a>.</p><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="App2">Configurations</h3><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="Sec43"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.1 </span>Classifiers</h3><p><i>River</i> was used in version 0.11.1. Both the Hoeffding tree and the naive Bayes classifiers were deployed using the default configuration.</p><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="Sec44"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.2 </span>Concept drift detector configurations</h3><h4 class="c-article__sub-heading c-article__sub-heading--small" id="Sec45"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.2.1 </span>BNDM</h4><ul class="u-list-style-bullet">
                      <li>
                        <p>const: 0.5, 1.0</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>max_depth: 2, 3</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>n_samples: 100, 250, 500, 1000</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>threshold: 0.45, 0.5, 0.55</p>
                      </li>
                    </ul><p>48 combinations (deterministic)</p><h4 class="c-article__sub-heading c-article__sub-heading--small" id="Sec46"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.2.2 </span>CSDDM</h4><ul class="u-list-style-bullet">
                      <li>
                        <p>confidence: 0.05, 0.01</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>feature_proportion: 0.1, 0.01</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>n_clusters: 2, 3</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>n_samples: 100, 250, 500, 1000</p>
                      </li>
                    </ul><p>32 combinations (non-deterministic <span class="mathjax-tex">\(\rightarrow \)</span> 160 runs)</p><h4 class="c-article__sub-heading c-article__sub-heading--small" id="Sec47"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.2.3 </span>D3</h4><ul class="u-list-style-bullet">
                      <li>
                        <p>n_reference_samples: 50, 125, 250, 500</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>n_recent_samples_proportion: 0.1, 0.5, 1.0</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>threshold: 0.6, 0.7, 0.8,</p>
                      </li>
                    </ul><p>36 combinations (non-deterministic <span class="mathjax-tex">\(\rightarrow \)</span> 180 runs)</p><h4 class="c-article__sub-heading c-article__sub-heading--small" id="Sec48"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.2.4 </span>IBDD</h4><ul class="u-list-style-bullet">
                      <li>
                        <p>n_consecutive_deviations: 1, 4</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>n_permutations: 10, 20, 40</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>n_samples: 100, 250, 500, 1000</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>update_interval: 50, 100, 250</p>
                      </li>
                    </ul><p>72 combinations (non-deterministic <span class="mathjax-tex">\(\rightarrow \)</span> 360 runs)</p><h4 class="c-article__sub-heading c-article__sub-heading--small" id="Sec49"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.2.5 </span>OCDD</h4><ul class="u-list-style-bullet">
                      <li>
                        <p>n_samples: 100, 250, 500, 1000</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>threshold: 0.2, 0.3, 0.4, 0.5</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>outlier detector: OneClassSVM (from sklearn)</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>outlier_detector_kwargs: {’nu’: 0.5, ’kernel’: ’rbf’, ’gamma’: ’auto’}</p>
                      </li>
                    </ul><p>16 combinations (deterministic)</p><h4 class="c-article__sub-heading c-article__sub-heading--small" id="Sec50"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.2.6 </span>SPLL</h4><ul class="u-list-style-bullet">
                      <li>
                        <p>n_clusters: 2, 3</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>n_samples: 100, 250, 500, 1000</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>threshold: 0.05, 0.005</p>
                      </li>
                    </ul><p>16 combinations (non-deterministic <span class="mathjax-tex">\(\rightarrow \)</span> 80 runs)</p><h4 class="c-article__sub-heading c-article__sub-heading--small" id="Sec51"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.2.7 </span>UDetect</h4><ul class="u-list-style-bullet">
                      <li>
                        <p>disjoint_training_windows: True</p><ul class="u-list-style-dash">
                          <li>
                            <p>n_samples: 50, 100, 250, 500</p>
                          </li>
                          <li>
                            <p>n_windows: 25, 50, 100</p>
                          </li>
                        </ul>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p>disjoint_training_windows: False</p><ul class="u-list-style-dash">
                          <li>
                            <p>n_samples: 100, 250, 500, 1000</p>
                          </li>
                          <li>
                            <p>n_windows: 50, 100, 250</p>
                          </li>
                        </ul>
                      </li>
                    </ul><p>12 + 15 = 24 combinations (deterministic)</p><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="Sec52"><span class="c-article-section__title-number">1.3 </span>Best configurations</h3><p>This appendix gives the configurations for the results highlighted in Tables <a data-track="click" data-track-label="link" data-track-action="table anchor" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y#Tab8">8</a>, <a data-track="click" data-track-label="link" data-track-action="table anchor" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y#Tab10">10</a> and <a data-track="click" data-track-label="link" data-track-action="table anchor" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y#Tab12">12</a>.</p><div class="c-article-section__figure js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="figure" data-container-section="figure" id="figure-8" data-title="Fig. 8"><figure><figcaption><b id="Fig8" class="c-article-section__figure-caption" data-test="figure-caption-text">Fig. 8</b></figcaption><div class="c-article-section__figure-content"><div class="c-article-section__figure-item"><picture class="c-article-section__figure-picture"><source type="image/webp" srcset="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1007%2Fs41060-024-00620-y/MediaObjects/41060_2024_620_Fig8_HTML.png?as=webp"><img aria-describedby="figure-8-desc" src="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1007%2Fs41060-024-00620-y/MediaObjects/41060_2024_620_Fig8_HTML.png" alt="Fig. 8" loading="lazy" width="685" height="503"></picture><div class="c-article-section__figure-link"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="article-link" data-track="click" data-track-label="button" data-track-action="view figure" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y/figures/8" data-track-dest="link:Figure8 Full size image" aria-label="Full size image figure 8" rel="nofollow"><span>Full size image</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></div><div class="c-article-section__figure-description" data-test="bottom-caption" id="figure-8-desc"><p>Accuracy increases with number of detected drifts until a certain point</p></div></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-table" data-test="inline-table" data-container-section="table" id="table-17"><figure><figcaption class="c-article-table__figcaption"><b id="Tab17" data-test="table-caption">Table 17 Best performing configurations of BNDM</b></figcaption><div class="u-text-right u-hide-print"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="table-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view table" data-track-label="button" rel="nofollow" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y/tables/17" aria-label="Full size table 17"><span>Full size table</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-table" data-test="inline-table" data-container-section="table" id="table-18"><figure><figcaption class="c-article-table__figcaption"><b id="Tab18" data-test="table-caption">Table 18 Best performing configurations of CSDDM</b></figcaption><div class="u-text-right u-hide-print"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="table-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view table" data-track-label="button" rel="nofollow" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y/tables/18" aria-label="Full size table 18"><span>Full size table</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-table" data-test="inline-table" data-container-section="table" id="table-19"><figure><figcaption class="c-article-table__figcaption"><b id="Tab19" data-test="table-caption">Table 19 Best performing configurations of D3</b></figcaption><div class="u-text-right u-hide-print"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="table-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view table" data-track-label="button" rel="nofollow" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y/tables/19" aria-label="Full size table 19"><span>Full size table</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-table" data-test="inline-table" data-container-section="table" id="table-20"><figure><figcaption class="c-article-table__figcaption"><b id="Tab20" data-test="table-caption">Table 20 Best performing configurations of IBDD</b></figcaption><div class="u-text-right u-hide-print"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="table-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view table" data-track-label="button" rel="nofollow" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y/tables/20" aria-label="Full size table 20"><span>Full size table</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-table" data-test="inline-table" data-container-section="table" id="table-21"><figure><figcaption class="c-article-table__figcaption"><b id="Tab21" data-test="table-caption">Table 21 Best performing configurations of OCDD</b></figcaption><div class="u-text-right u-hide-print"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="table-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view table" data-track-label="button" rel="nofollow" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y/tables/21" aria-label="Full size table 21"><span>Full size table</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-table" data-test="inline-table" data-container-section="table" id="table-22"><figure><figcaption class="c-article-table__figcaption"><b id="Tab22" data-test="table-caption">Table 22 Best performing configurations of SPLL</b></figcaption><div class="u-text-right u-hide-print"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="table-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view table" data-track-label="button" rel="nofollow" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y/tables/22" aria-label="Full size table 22"><span>Full size table</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-table" data-test="inline-table" data-container-section="table" id="table-23"><figure><figcaption class="c-article-table__figcaption"><b id="Tab23" data-test="table-caption">Table 23 Best performing configurations of UDetect</b></figcaption><div class="u-text-right u-hide-print"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="table-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view table" data-track-label="button" rel="nofollow" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y/tables/23" aria-label="Full size table 23"><span>Full size table</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></figure></div><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="App3">Figures</h3><p>This appendix contains figures detailing how the number of detected drifts affects accuracy and <i>lift-per-drift</i>.</p><p>On all but two data streams, detecting more frequently increases the Hoeffding tree’s accuracy until a certain point. On <i>Poker Hands</i> and <i>Outdoor Objects</i> the accuracy keeps increasing with the number of detected drifts, as the data streams are mostly ordered (cf. Sect. <a data-track="click" data-track-label="link" data-track-action="section anchor" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y#Sec31">6.3</a>).</p><p>On all data streams detecting less frequently increases <i>lift-per-drift</i> measured on the Hoeffding tree classifiers in a graph that resembles a negative exponential or logarithmic behavior with a few minor outliers.</p><div class="c-article-section__figure js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="figure" data-container-section="figure" id="figure-9" data-title="Fig. 9"><figure><figcaption><b id="Fig9" class="c-article-section__figure-caption" data-test="figure-caption-text">Fig. 9</b></figcaption><div class="c-article-section__figure-content"><div class="c-article-section__figure-item"><picture class="c-article-section__figure-picture"><source type="image/webp" srcset="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1007%2Fs41060-024-00620-y/MediaObjects/41060_2024_620_Fig9_HTML.png?as=webp"><img aria-describedby="figure-9-desc" src="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1007%2Fs41060-024-00620-y/MediaObjects/41060_2024_620_Fig9_HTML.png" alt="Fig. 9" loading="lazy" width="685" height="503"></picture><div class="c-article-section__figure-link"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="article-link" data-track="click" data-track-label="button" data-track-action="view figure" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y/figures/9" data-track-dest="link:Figure9 Full size image" aria-label="Full size image figure 9" rel="nofollow"><span>Full size image</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></div><div class="c-article-section__figure-description" data-test="bottom-caption" id="figure-9-desc"><p>Accuracy increases with number of detected drifts until a certain point</p></div></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-section__figure js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="figure" data-container-section="figure" id="figure-10" data-title="Fig. 10"><figure><figcaption><b id="Fig10" class="c-article-section__figure-caption" data-test="figure-caption-text">Fig. 10</b></figcaption><div class="c-article-section__figure-content"><div class="c-article-section__figure-item"><picture class="c-article-section__figure-picture"><source type="image/webp" srcset="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1007%2Fs41060-024-00620-y/MediaObjects/41060_2024_620_Fig10_HTML.png?as=webp"><img aria-describedby="figure-10-desc" src="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1007%2Fs41060-024-00620-y/MediaObjects/41060_2024_620_Fig10_HTML.png" alt="Fig. 10" loading="lazy" width="685" height="503"></picture><div class="c-article-section__figure-link"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="article-link" data-track="click" data-track-label="button" data-track-action="view figure" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y/figures/10" data-track-dest="link:Figure10 Full size image" aria-label="Full size image figure 10" rel="nofollow"><span>Full size image</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></div><div class="c-article-section__figure-description" data-test="bottom-caption" id="figure-10-desc"><p>Accuracy increases with number of detected drifts until a certain point</p></div></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-section__figure js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="figure" data-container-section="figure" id="figure-11" data-title="Fig. 11"><figure><figcaption><b id="Fig11" class="c-article-section__figure-caption" data-test="figure-caption-text">Fig. 11</b></figcaption><div class="c-article-section__figure-content"><div class="c-article-section__figure-item"><picture class="c-article-section__figure-picture"><source type="image/webp" srcset="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1007%2Fs41060-024-00620-y/MediaObjects/41060_2024_620_Fig11_HTML.png?as=webp"><img aria-describedby="figure-11-desc" src="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1007%2Fs41060-024-00620-y/MediaObjects/41060_2024_620_Fig11_HTML.png" alt="Fig. 11" loading="lazy" width="685" height="503"></picture><div class="c-article-section__figure-link"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="article-link" data-track="click" data-track-label="button" data-track-action="view figure" href="/article/10.1007/s41060-024-00620-y/figures/11" data-track-dest="link:Figure11 Full size image" aria-label="Full size image figure 11" rel="nofollow"><span>Full size image</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></div><div class="c-article-section__figure-description" data-test="bottom-caption" id="figure-11-desc"><p>Accuracy increases with number of detected drifts until a certain point</p></div></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-section__figure js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="figure" data-container-section="figure" id="figure-12" data-title="Fig. 12"><figure><figcaption><b id="Fig12" class="c-article-section__figure-caption" data-test="figure-caption-text">Fig. 12</b></figcaption><div class="c-article-section__figure-content"><div class="c-article-section__figure-item"><picture class="c-article-section__figure-picture"><source type="image/webp" srcset="//media.springernature.com/lw6